herramientas: -Due to the sensitivity of customer related requirements, U.S. Citizenship is required.-Candidate must have a master's degree in a specialized field plus a minimum of 4 years of applicable experience; or, a bachelor's degree in the specialized field plus 5 years of applicable experience; or, a bachelor's degree in any field with a minimum of 7 years of specialized experience.-Must have a Top Secret clearance.-Candidate will provide subject matter expertise in the system engineering technical review (SETR) process and through each adaptive acquisition framework pathway.-Must have thorough understanding of engineering principles and analyze a wide range of technology principles.-Must have familiarity with security requirements (e.g., anti-tamper, exportability features, supply chain risk management, secure design, defense-in-depth and cybersecurity implementation) required.-Must have DAU Courses such as ACQ 160 or ENG 260 or equivalent experience.-Must have a DoD Top Secret Clearance
descripcion: At The Wise Seeker, we're seeking a System Security Engineer subject matter expert (e.g. anti-tamper, exportability features, and secure design) to represent program protection equities in the system engineering technical review (SETR) process to ensure adequate protection measures are incorporated across the entire customer portfolio and throughout each’s product’s lifecycle.The System Security Engineer (SSE) will provide Technology Protection and engineering assistance to an Army acquisition program. Apply scientific and engineering principles to identify security vulnerabilities in hardware, software, or firmware and develop risks and mitigations associated with these vulnerabilities. Position will play a key role in protecting critical technology and recommending appropriate countermeasures and program protection strategies.Tasks-Document program protection planning in the systems engineering plan (SEP), program protection plan (PPP) and system security plan (SSP).-Analyze and assist engineering and program management with program protection requirements analysis.-Provide technical support to identify vulnerabilities for CPI, mission critical functions, mission critical components, and recommend appropriate security controls.-Support system threat assessments, vulnerability identification, security risk analysis, and security test and evaluation.-Provide System Security Engineer subject matter expertise in meetings, system engineering technical review (SETR) process, and through each adaptive acquisition framework pathway.
funciones: ['Técnico de Seguridad', 'Técnico de Sistemas', 'Categoría o nivelTécnico']

descripcion: ¡Únete a Nuestro Equipo como Desarrollador de Plantillas de Informes en Barcelona!Desde la oficina de Crit Sabadell, estamos en la búsqueda de un Desarrollador de Plantillas de Informes para incorporarse al equipo de nuestro cliente, una destacada plataforma de gestión integral de centros educativos que forma parte de un importante grupo finlandés de comunicación y edición.Descripción del Rol: El candidato ideal poseerá un sólido dominio de la herramienta Stimulsoft y experiencia en el diseño y desarrollo de plantillas de reporting. Además, deberá destacar por sus habilidades analíticas, capacidad de resolución de problemas y atención al detalle.Responsabilidades: Colaborar con Product Owners (PO) y el equipo técnico para comprender los requisitos de los informes y asegurar una interpretación precisa. Diseñar, desarrollar y mantener plantillas de reporting utilizando Stimulsoft, garantizando una presentación visualmente atractiva de datos y gráficos. Implementar lógica de negocios en las plantillas para asegurar la precisión y coherencia de los datos. Optimizar y mejorar el rendimiento de las plantillas para una generación rápida y eficiente de informes. Colaborar con el equipo de desarrollo de APIs para obtener datos necesarios y garantizar una integración fluida. Realizar pruebas exhaustivas de las plantillas para asegurar funcionalidad y calidad. Documentar claramente el diseño y la funcionalidad para facilitar mantenimiento y futuras mejoras. Mantenerse actualizado con las mejores prácticas y nuevas características de StimulsoftBeneficios: Salario según experiencia aportada Horario flexible de 8 a 9 h de entrada y de 17 a 18 h de salida. 1 día en la oficina y 4 días de teletrabajo. Oportunidad de trabajar en un entorno dinámico y desafiante.

descripcion: ¿Tienes experiencia como desarrolador de plantillas de informes?Desde la oficina de Crit Sabadell, estamos buscando un Desarrollador de plantillas de informes para unirse al equipo de nuestro cliente ubicado en Barcelona.Nuestro cliente, es una importante plataforma de gestión integral de centros educativos que pertenece a un gran grupo Finlandés de comunicación y edición.Descripción: El candidato ideal tendrá un sólido conocimiento de la herramienta Stimulsoft y experiencia en el diseño y desarrollo de plantillas de reporting. Implementar lógica de negocios en las plantillas de informes para garantizar la precisión y coherencia de los datos mostrados. Habilidades en el manejo de lenguajes de marcado y estilos (por ejemplo, XML, CSS) para personalizar la apariencia de los informes. Conocimiento en el manejo de datos y lógica de negocios para garantizar la precisión y relevancia de los informes generados. Conocimientos nivel medio de inglés.Beneficios: Salario competitivo. Horario flexible entrada de 8 a 9 h y salida de 17 a 18 h. 1 días oficina y 4 días de teletrabajo. descripcion: At The Wise Seeker, we're seeking a System Security Engineer subject matter expert (e.g. anti-tamper, exportability features, and secure design) to represent program protection equities in the system engineering technical review (SETR) process to ensure adequate protection measures are incorporated across the entire customer portfolio and throughout each’s product’s lifecycle.The System Security Engineer (SSE) will provide Technology Protection and engineering assistance to an Army acquisition program. Apply scientific and engineering principles to identify security vulnerabilities in hardware, software, or firmware and develop risks and mitigations associated with these vulnerabilities. Position will play a key role in protecting critical technology and recommending appropriate countermeasures and program protection strategies.Tasks-Document program protection planning in the systems engineering plan (SEP), program protection plan (PPP) and system security plan (SSP).-Analyze and assist engineering and program management with program protection requirements analysis.-Provide technical support to identify vulnerabilities for CPI, mission critical functions, mission critical components, and recommend appropriate security controls.-Support system threat assessments, vulnerability identification, security risk analysis, and security test and evaluation.-Provide System Security Engineer subject matter expertise in meetings, system engineering technical review (SETR) process, and through each adaptive acquisition framework pathway.

descripcion: At The Wise Seeker, we're seeking a System Security Engineer subject matter expert (e.g. anti-tamper, exportability features, and secure design) to represent program protection equities in the system engineering technical review (SETR) process to ensure adequate protection measures are incorporated across the entire customer portfolio and throughout each’s product’s lifecycle.The System Security Engineer (SSE) will provide Technology Protection and engineering assistance to an Army acquisition program. Apply scientific and engineering principles to identify security vulnerabilities in hardware, software, or firmware and develop risks and mitigations associated with these vulnerabilities. Position will play a key role in protecting critical technology and recommending appropriate countermeasures and program protection strategies.Tasks-Document program protection planning in the systems engineering plan (SEP), program protection plan (PPP) and system security plan (SSP).-Analyze and assist engineering and program management with program protection requirements analysis.-Provide technical support to identify vulnerabilities for CPI, mission critical functions, mission critical components, and recommend appropriate security controls.-Support system threat assessments, vulnerability identification, security risk analysis, and security test and evaluation.-Provide System Security Engineer subject matter expertise in meetings, system engineering technical review (SETR) process, and through each adaptive acquisition framework pathway.

Apply scientific and engineering principles to identify security vulnerabilities in hardware, software, or firmware and develop risks and mitigations associated with these vulnerabilities. Position will play a key role in protecting critical technology and recommending appropriate countermeasures and program protection strategies.Tasks-Document program protection planning in the systems engineering plan (SEP), program protection plan (PPP) and system security plan (SSP).-Analyze and assist engineering and program management with program protection requirements analysis.-Provide technical support to identify vulnerabilities for CPI, mission critical functions, mission critical components, and recommend appropriate security controls.-Support system threat assessments, vulnerability identification, security risk analysis, and security test and evaluation.-Provide System Security Engineer subject matter expertise in meetings, system engineering technical review (SETR) process, and through each adaptive acquisition framework pathway.

descripcion: As a team member of the PMO, will be responsible ofmanaging projects to implement or enhance systems and processes for mulOple areas of the company. Also he will have to ensure project deliverables are within the de?ned quality.  Project Planning: Develop a detailed project plan that includes defining objectives, scope, timelines, required resources, and budget.  Resource Management: Assign tasks and responsibilities to team members, ensuring they have the necessary resources to carry out their functions.  Progress Monitoring: Oversee project progress to ensure deadlines are met and established milestones are achieved.  Risk Management: Identify and assess potential project risks, develop mitigation strategies, and be prepared to address unforeseen issues.  Communication: Keep all stakeholders informed about project progress, potential issues, and implemented solutions.  Team Coordination: Facilitate collaboration among team members and ensure effective communication.  Problem Solving: Address problems and challenges that arise during the project, seeking effective solutions and minimizing negative impacts.
